/*

Modules are the reusable, modular parts of our design. They are the callouts, the sidebar sections, the product lists and so on. This is where the majority of your styles will go.

Examples of Module Styles:

    .folder {
        padding: 5px;
    }
    .folder-name {
        color: #FFF;
    }
    .folder-items {
        background: url(icon.png);
    }

Examples of Subclassing Modules:

    .pod { 
        width: 100%; 
    } 
    .pod input[type=text] { 
        width: 50%; 
    }

    .pod-constrained input[type=text] {
        width: 100%; 
    }

    .pod-callout { 
        width: 200px; 
    }
    .pod-callout input[type=text] { 
        width: 180px; 
    }

Usage of a sublcass in HTML would look like this:
    
    <div class="pod">...</div>
    <div class="pod pod-constrained">...</div>
    <div class="pod pod-callout">...</div> 

*/

